```c
int next_char(int* input, int length) {
  static int index = 0;
  if (index < length) {
    return input[index++];
  }
  return -1;  // Return -1 to indicate the end of the array
}
```

This would ensure that `next_char()` never goes out of bounds, even if the input array is empty. 

Then, in the `main()` function, you would pass the length of `input` as a parameter to `next_char()`:

```c
