  int nchars = 100;
  for (int index = 0; index < nchars; index++) {
    if (next_char(input, nchars) == ' ') {
      break;
    }
  }
  return 0;
}
```

This is a more thorough fix because it addresses the root cause of the issue by preventing `next_char()` from going out of bounds in the first place.















